take the day off.

283
00:16:28,404 --> 00:16:29,905
(ALL CHEER)

284
00:16:34,452 --> 00:16:36,703
-Will you stop that?
-(WORKERS YELP)

285
00:16:37,955 --> 00:16:39,956
Thank you, Mr. Scrooge.

286
00:16:41,751 --> 00:16:43,585
Be here all the earlier the next morning.

287
00:16:43,670 --> 00:16:45,962
WORKER: Okay. You bet. First thing.

288
00:16:49,592 --> 00:16:51,677
With their employer gone at last,

289
00:16:51,761 --> 00:16:54,471
Bob Cratchit and the bookkeepers
immediately began

290
00:16:54,555 --> 00:16:59,142
that most pleasant of activities,
the celebration of Christmas.

291
00:16:59,936 --> 00:17:02,062
-He's gone!
-(WORKERS CHEER)

292
